                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                    <ref target="#ms_i1.1 #ms_i1.2 #ms_i1.3"/>
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                    <ref target="#ms_i1.4 #ms_i1.5"/>
                    <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>Columetric layout: <locus target="#86v" facs="091">fols. 86v, </locus> (Ps. 150); <locus target="#93v #94r" facs="098">93v, 94r</locus> (tenth biblical canticle)</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003">Fol. iiv(erso)</locus><desc>Crude drawing in pencil of an Ethiopian Church</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#iiir(ecto)" facs="003">Fol. iiir(ecto)</locus><desc>Crude drawing in pencil of two figures</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#112v" facs="117">Fol. 112v</locus><desc>Crude drawings in pencil of faces</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d4"><locus target="#113r" facs="117">Fol. 113r</locus><desc>top: <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1066DavidHarp">David Playing the Harp</ref>, with an attendant holding an umbrella</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d5"><locus target="#113r" facs="117">Fol. 113r</locus><desc>bottom: Three figures. The ones on left and right are smaller. The one on the left hold spear and shield; the one on the right holds a sword and has the caption “sword bearer” over it. The large figure in the center looks regal, with elaborate robes and a beard</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d6">
                      <locus target="#ivv(erso)" facs="005">Fol. ivv(erso)</locus> practice ḥarägs
                    </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d7">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#1r #6r #10v #11r #16v #23v #30r #34v #41r #49r #55r #59r #67v #75v #78r #82v #87r #96v #101r" facs="005 010 015 021 028 034 039 045 053 059 063 072 080 082 087 091 101 105">folss. 1r, 6r, 10v, 11r, 16v, 23v, 30r, 34v, 41r, 49r, 55r, 59r, 67v, 75v, 78r, 82v, 87r, 96v, 101r, </locus> (ḥaräg);
                      <locus target="#58v" facs="063">58v, </locus> (crosses made of full stops);
                      <locus target="#109r" facs="113">109r, </locus> (multiple full stops);
                      <locus target="#112r" facs="116">112r</locus> (lines of full stops and alternating red and black dots)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a1">
                      <desc type="GuestText">
                      <locus target="#iiiv(erso)" facs="004">Fol. iiiv(erso)</locus> Introduction to the Psalms
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e1">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#ir(etco) #iv(erso)" facs="001 002">Fols. ir(etco), iv(erso)</locus> pen trials
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e2">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#iir(ecto)" facs="002">Fol. iir(ecto)</locus> blank
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e3">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#iiir(ecto)" facs="003">Fols. iiir(ecto), </locus> The psalter was begun on this folio, but abandoned and erased and begun again on <locus target="#1r" facs="005">1r</locus>
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e4">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#ivr(ecto)" facs="004">Fol. ivr(ecto)</locus>: scrawls
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e5">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#45v" facs="050">Fol. 45v</locus> A two-word text “here is half” surrounded in red and black ink, marks the midpoint of the psalms
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="a2">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#113v" facs="118">Fol. 113v</locus> beginning of Trinitarian formula
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e7">
                      <desc>
                      The back cover has a recessed niche in which there was probably a mirror at one time
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e8">
                        <locus target="#3v #9r #23v #31v" facs="008 013 028 036">Fols. 3v, 9r, 23v, 31v</locus>
                      <desc>etc., words of text are written interlinearly</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e9">
                        <locus target="#25r #31v #37r #56v" facs="029 036 041 061">Fols. 25r, 31v, 37r, 56v</locus>
                        <desc>etc., and lines of text are written interlinearly</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e10">
                        <locus target="#37r" facs="041">f. 37r, line 11</locus>
                        <desc>lines of text are written in the upper margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e11">
                        <locus target="#8v #88v" facs="013 093">Fols. 8v, 88v</locus>
                        <desc>erasure markings are visible</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e12">
                        <locus target="#70v" facs="075">Fol. 70v</locus>
                        <desc>, e.g., text has been removed</desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e13">
                      <desc>
                      The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate
                      aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. Where the line is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above
                      or below the end of the line (throughout)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                    <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Parchment, 200 x 125 x 50 mm, four Coptic chain stitches attached with bridle attachments to rough-hewn boards of the traditional wood, inside front board covered with tooled leather.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="parchment"/>
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="leather"/>
                        </decoNote>
                    </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
